
[1]forgery

   FORGERY, n.

   1. The act of forging or working metal into shape. In this sense,
   rarely or never now used.

   2. The act of falsifying; the crime of counterfeiting; as the forgery
   of coin, or of bank notes, or of a bond. Forgery may consist in
   counterfeiting a writing, or in setting a false name to it, to the
   prejudice of another person.

   3. That which is forged or counterfeited. Certain letters, purporting
   to be written by Gen. Washington, during the revolution, were
   forgeries.
